<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<!--
  Canonical entitlements file for the VibeYTM macOS app.

  Sprint 0 (this commit): the file lives here ready for Xcode 26 to
  reference once `app/VibeYTM.xcodeproj` lands (see app/README.md "Status
  Sprint 0 Task 1 — partial"). Until Xcode is installed, `app/build.sh`
  uses its own inline copy (see step [4/5] of that script). Both files
  must stay in sync; the inline copy is a temporary measure.

  Why two copies: Xcode wants entitlements as a project-referenced file;
  build.sh works without Xcode at all and inlines them. They're identical
  in content. When Xcode 26 lands and the .xcodeproj is created, point
  Xcode's Signing & Capabilities at THIS file and delete the inline copy
  from build.sh (or leave both — duplication is annoying but harmless).
-->
<dict>
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key><true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key><true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key><true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.network.client</key><true/>
  <!--
    App Group entitlement INTENTIONALLY ABSENT until Developer ID
    signing is in place. Declaring this entitlement on an ad-hoc-signed
    bundle causes macOS Tahoe to prompt the user on every launch
    ("VibeYTM wants to access data beyond its own folder") AND prevents
    the SwiftUI main window from coming forward properly. Verified
    empirically (Sprint 0 follow-up, commit 709bd6b regression).

    Re-enable when paying for Apple Developer Program (Sprint 6 cutover)
    by uncommenting the block below — and apply the same change to
    app/build.sh's inline entitlements block:

      <key>com.apple.security.application-groups</key>
      <array>
        <string>group.com.vibeytm.dev</string>
      </array>

    SharedPlaybackSnapshotWriter handles the missing container
    gracefully (logs once, skips writes) until then.
  -->
</dict>
</plist>
